    "title": "Permissionless rebalances trust manipulable thin-liquidity market caps",
    "locations": [
      "0x120c6956d292b800a835cb935c9dd326bdb4e011/temp-contracts/MarketCapSortedTokenCategories.sol:206",
      "0x120c6956d292b800a835cb935c9dd326bdb4e011/temp-contracts/MarketCapSortedTokenCategories.sol:235",
      "0x120c6956d292b800a835cb935c9dd326bdb4e011/temp-contracts/MarketCapSqrtController.sol:437",
      "0x120c6956d292b800a835cb935c9dd326bdb4e011/temp-contracts/MarketCapSqrtController.sol:486",
      "0x120c6956d292b800a835cb935c9dd326bdb4e011/temp-contracts/lib/MCapSqrtLibrary.sol:64"
    ],
    "claim": "The controller picks constituents and weights from `totalSupply * Uniswap TWAP price` without any liquidity floor, depth check, or manipulation circuit breaker. Because both category sorting and pool rebalances are permissionless, an attacker can move a shallow token/WETH pair over the oracle window, force that token into the top set or an outsized weight, and then trade against the pool at the manipulated valuation.",
    "impact": "A low-liquidity constituent can be made to look systemically important, causing the pool to buy it or overweight it and letting the attacker drain more valuable pool assets through subsequent swaps/arbitrage.",
    "paths": [
      "Accumulate or create a thin-liquidity token already present in a category",
      "Push its WETH TWAP upward over the long oracle window",
      "Call `orderCategoryTokensByMarketCap`",
      "Call `reindexPool` or `reweighPool`",
      "Sell the overpriced token into the index pool or buy out underweighted real assets"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "F-002",
    "severity": "High",
    "confidence": "medium",
    "title": "Instantaneous `totalSupply()` reads let flash-mintable or rebase tokens spoof market cap",
    "locations": [
      "0x120c6956d292b800a835cb935c9dd326bdb4e011/temp-contracts/MarketCapSortedTokenCategories.sol:235",
      "0x120c6956d292b800a835cb935c9dd326bdb4e011/temp-contracts/MarketCapSortedTokenCategories.sol:252",
      "0x120c6956d292b800a835cb935c9dd326bdb4e011/temp-contracts/lib/MCapSqrtLibrary.sol:29",
      "0x120c6956d292b800a835cb935c9dd326bdb4e011/temp-contracts/lib/MCapSqrtLibrary.sol:44",
      "0x120c6956d292b800a835cb935c9dd326bdb4e011/temp-contracts/lib/MCapSqrtLibrary.sol:64"
    ],
    "claim": "Market-cap and weight calculations read `IERC20(token).totalSupply()` at execution time instead of using any supply snapshot or time average. A flash-mintable, rebasing, or governance-mintable token can therefore report an arbitrarily large temporary supply during sorting/rebalance and be treated as a top-cap asset even though the extra supply is not durable economic value.",
    "impact": "An attacker can temporarily inflate a token's reported market cap, force it into the index or give it a much larger target weight, and then unwind the fake supply after the pool has accepted the distorted composition.",
    "paths": [
      "Mint or flash-mint a huge temporary supply for a category token",
      "Call `orderCategoryTokensByMarketCap` while supply is inflated",
      "Call `reindexPool` or `reweighPool` before burning/resetting supply",
      "Exploit the pool's new composition/weights to extract value"
    ]
  },
