    ],
    "claim": "`updateMinimumBalance` is externally callable by anyone and mutates pool state using `_estimatePoolValue`, which trusts `extrapolatePoolValueFromToken()` plus a short-window oracle on a single reference token. An attacker can manipulate that reference valuation and immediately force a much larger minimum balance for an unready token.",
    "impact": "Newly added tokens can be kept perpetually unready or require unrealistic acquisition targets, causing prolonged denial of service around reindexing and potentially forcing the pool into harmful reconfiguration behavior.",
    "paths": [
      "Wait until a token is added but not yet `ready`",
      "Manipulate the token/price source used by `extrapolatePoolValueFromToken()` over the short oracle window",
      "Call `updateMinimumBalance(pool, token)`",
      "The pool now requires an unreachable minimum balance before the token can become usable"
    ]
  },
