      "0x120c6956d292b800a835cb935c9dd326bdb4e011/temp-contracts/OwnableProxy.sol:82"
    ],
    "claim": "Ownership initialization is exposed through public `initialize()` functions that simply call `_initializeOwnership()`. `OwnableProxy` only locks the implementation contract in its constructor; a freshly deployed proxy starts with `_owner == address(0)`. If deployment does not atomically initialize the proxy, any account can front-run the intended admin and become owner.",
    "impact": "A successful first-call takeover gives full control over category curation, pool deployment, fee recipients, seller parameters, controller pointers, and governance delegation from pools.",
    "paths": [
      "Deploy a proxy pointing at `MarketCapSqrtController` or `MarketCapSortedTokenCategories`",
      "Before the legitimate admin initializes it, attacker calls `initialize()`",
      "Attacker becomes owner and can execute all owner-only admin flows"
    ]
  },
