    "claim": "`prepareIndexPool` stores `categoryID` as `uint16` without checking bounds. Once `categoryIndex` exceeds 65535, newly prepared pools silently wrap to a different category and later reindex against the wrong token set.",
    "impact": "Future pools can be rebalanced using unintended assets, creating misconfiguration, denial of service, or fund misallocation for those pools.",
